Project name: 
Inventory.py
(Shoe inventory program)

Description:
The code featured in the remote repository does the following for a shoe shop
1.Gets the cost of the shoe and total value
2.Gets the quantity and highest quantity of shoes
3.Reads the shoes data and captures it (Via the txt file)
4.To view all the shoes and to find a specific shoe
5.Which shoes need to be restocked and also the amount the shoe shop has in stock of each shoe.
6.The user can also add and remove shoes if needed.

It has been all neatly organised in a menu for the user as seen below.

if there are any question’s please feel free to ask.

